Brendan Rodgers has been convicted of leaving a property in Accrington to rot . 
  The Liverpool manager was ordered to pay £400 and £375 costs . 
  Rodgers and his business partner Judith O'Hagan were found guilty of ignoring an improvement notice issued by Hyndburn Council . 
  The house was left in a state of disrepair for three years . 
  Rodgers had been ordered to fix the windows and doors . 
  Liverpool lost 2-1 to Aston Villa in the FA Cup at Wembley on Sunday . 
 